metadata.name: TRASH Erector V 2.0 #5
metadata.description:
TRASH Erector V 2.0 is a generative #trashart project by video artist INA VARE following TRASH Erector V 1.0 which was dropped earlier in 2022.  
In this edition, everything is bigger, bolder, and pixelated. Every scene opens with a blast. Literary. Elements are created from analog glitched photos and special effects videos finalized as dithered gifs. The background is hand-drawn pixel-art tiles moved and animated by coding. 

Each piece is generated within a wide range of predefined rarity features both visual and creative coding.

-> Click on the image to hide and erect the trash.

The project includes a range of Common, Rare, and Legendary trash attributes like:

- Background Colors 
‚Äì Tile Design and Tracery
‚Äì Background Animations
- Explosions
- Trash Items
- Totters
- Framing

Each feature has weighted rarities and might include variations of none.

Any hints to known personas, events, and nonsense is not a coincidence.


Project by INA VARE, 2022.
Coding: Metimus

metadata.name: Elasticity #37
metadata.description:
Elasticity is a collection that explores the ambiguity of discrete continuity in architecture.

Elasticity is a tectonic, generative system that combines simple, discrete parts into an elastic relationship between part and whole, creating a discrete and continuous elastic form. A form that celebrates the continuity of digital variation while respecting a discrete approach to a digital whole.

It is a generative follow-up to the project CM.CollabWood, where the same parts were embedded in a real-time participatory architectural environment, where clusters of parts were placed by participants in real-time in collective design sessions to create tangible collective open forms.

___________________________________________________
Controls:
‚Ä¢ 'P' pause/play animation
‚Ä¢ 'B' monochrome mode (wait a bit for recalculation)

Resize Canvas in live/open mode:
(press once and wait for recalculation!)
‚Ä¢ 'DoubleClick' go Fullscreen
‚Ä¢ '1' square 1024x1024
‚Ä¢ '2' square 2048x2048
‚Ä¢ '3' square 3072x3072
‚Ä¢ '4' square 4096x4096 (might not work on all laptops)
‚Ä¢ '5' landscape 4000x3000
‚Ä¢ '6' portrait 3000x4000
‚Ä¢ '7' fullHD 1920x1080
‚Ä¢ '8' UHD 3840 x 2160
‚Ä¢ '9' square small(for sharing a gif on twitter) 512x512
‚Ä¢ '0' flex. adapt to current window size

Save & Export in live/open mode:
‚Ä¢ 's' save a .png of in current resolution
‚Ä¢ 'g' save a seamless loop .gif in current resolution
(press the key and wait for export, might take some time, consider with higher resolutions files get pretty big)

Steps to save a gif/png :
‚Ä¢ go in live/open mode (wait)
‚Ä¢ resize canvas to your desired resolution (wait)
‚Ä¢ press s or g and wait for recalculation & download to finish
‚Ä¢ enjoy elasticity :)

metadata.name: Do Touch #144
metadata.description:
o History tells us an isolated system tends to evolve from order to disorder, and from this disorder beauty arises. Chaos builds over time, ultimately perishing and a new cycle emerges. In the chaos, one may want to embrace a moment and will need to intervene to preserve the dynamics.
o This project assembles the progress, with triangle grids inter-linked with each other and influenced by the environment‚Äôs forces. The movement speeds up over time, and the art piece system will run into chaos unless an interaction is made.
o This project is a cooperation between the artist and the viewer. The artist sets the art system's behavior and the viewer intervenes to express his/her preference. Do touch, do intervene.

Touch keys:
o View construction steps: press number keys 1,2,3,4 to see steps
o Static view: q to pause movement, w to resume
o Push: use arrow key up, down, left, right to push the triangles
o Comfort speed zone: press 0 to let them range bound in current speed
o Accelerate or decelerate the chaos: - to slow things down, = to increase movement
o ‚ÄúI am done, free them‚Äù: press f key to free the triangles to roam outside of the canvas

This project consists of Mini sets:
o Pop: bold palette
o Classic: retro palette
o Day Dream: soft n romantic palette
o Vanilla: time-lapse color background, no shades
o Sonata: black n white keys
o Paper: white background, no shades

metadata.name: UPLOAD.EXE #70
metadata.description:
No death in the metaverse 
100 billion mortal coils before us, reduced to silly memes 

Here then, a chance to right every wrong 
Or curse ourselves, forgetting we once counted days so keenly

&notilt=true : Remove tilt-shift filter

metadata.name: Rimal #439
metadata.description:
A manifestation of elemental simplicity and tactile potential, the abstract sand plate transcends its granular composition to embody a realm of dynamic abstraction. As a textured canvas, it defies permanence, inviting fluidity and transformation in response to the whims of creation, science, therapy, and education.

In the artistic spectrum, the abstract sand plate becomes an ever-shifting tableau where the interplay of hands orchestrates ephemeral masterpieces. Here, the grains of sand, liberated from fixity, participate in an intricate dance of form and impermanence, blurring the lines between creation and dissolution.

metadata.name: Kiss #4
metadata.description:
With gravity boundless - and within; memories of suns long since passed - a terminal dance unfolds.

Process: Forged in Hydra.

‚ö†Ô∏è The longer you spend with this piece, the deeper it becomes.

üåê A note on rarity and variety: 

Although there are many variations possible within this piece, they are on the subtler side.

As this is a highly temporal piece, these variations ask you to dive into the experience of the piece in order to fully appreciate them. Please proceed bearing this in mind.

Experiment with the aspect ratio of this piece using the ‚Äòopen live‚Äô function below the viewport - it can be enjoyed elastically. A square frame provides a more formal experience, while a widescreen view provides a deeper experience.
